Senate Resolution 277
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Essie Frankie Mae Stegall Arnold; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Essie Frankie Mae Stegall Arnold on January 26, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Essie Frankie Mae Stegall Arnold was born on April 10, 1930, in Newnan,
5 Georgia, a beloved daughter of Essie Mae and Milton Stegall; and
6 WHEREAS, she was baptized at an early age at Dent Chapel A.M.E. Church and remained
7 steadfast in her faith throughout her life, later becoming a devoted member of Saint John
8 A.M.E. Church, where she served as a stewardess, an officer on the Steward Board, and a
9 member of the Missionary Board Society; and
10 WHEREAS, Essie Frankie Mae Stegall Arnold dedicated nearly 50 years of her life to
11 serving the City of Fairburn, Georgia, where she worked, volunteered, and contributed to
12 many schools, churches, and nonprofit organizations, enriching the lives of countless
13 individuals in her community; and
